            {'rank':16,'student_name':'Sparsh Sahni','school_name':'Amity International School, Gurgaon','idea_title':'Tinkle Bite: Invisible Hearing Assistance Through Oral Implants','idea_description':'An innovative hearing aid designed as an oral implant, reducing social stigma while improving hearing capabilities.','problem_statement':'Many individuals with hearing impairments avoid traditional hearing aids due to social stigma and visibility concerns, limiting access to effective hearing support.','proposed_solution':'Tinkle Bite is an innovative hearing aid designed as an oral implant. The discreet solution improves hearing capabilities while reducing social stigma, helping users communicate confidently and comfortably.','tags':['SDG 3 - Good Health and Well-being','SDG 10 - Reduced Inequalities'],'season':'Season 5'},
            {'rank':17,'student_name':'Krish Bhatnagar','school_name':'Amity International School','idea_title':'Saathi: Inclusive Learning Platform for Children with Special Needs','idea_description':'A dedicated application supporting children with special needs through customized learning and engagement tools.','problem_statement':'Children with special needs often require personalized support systems that are not readily available through conventional educational platforms.','proposed_solution':'Saathi is a dedicated application designed to support children with special needs through customized learning, engagement, and assistance tools. The platform addresses diverse requirements and ensures that every child has access to meaningful learning opportunities.','tags':['SDG 4 - Quality Education','SDG 10 - Reduced Inequalities'],'season':'Season 5'},
