            {'rank':21,'student_name':'Abhay Shreeshail Pharsiyawar','school_name':'Basaveshwara International Public School, Bagalkote','idea_title':'Driving Distraction Disabler: Smart Technology for Safer Roads','idea_description':'An integrated road safety system combining alcohol detection, drowsiness alerts, emotion recognition, and aggressive driving detection.','problem_statement':'Driver distraction remains one of the leading causes of road accidents worldwide. Factors such as fatigue, alcohol consumption, emotional distress, and unsafe driving behaviors significantly increase the risk of collisions.','proposed_solution':'Driving Distraction Disabler is an integrated road safety system that combines alcohol detection, seatbelt monitoring, drowsiness alerts, emotion recognition, and aggressive driving detection. Powered by sensors, GPS, and machine learning algorithms, the system continuously monitors driver behavior and provides timely alerts.','tags':['SDG 3 - Good Health and Well-being','SDG 11 - Sustainable Cities and Communities'],'season':'Season 5'},
