            {'rank':23,'student_name':'Aman Shandilya & Divij Bansal','school_name':'Not Specified','idea_title':'Sustainable Greens: Smart Greenhouse for Modern Agriculture','idea_description':'A smart greenhouse that automatically monitors and adjusts environmental conditions using sensors and automation.','problem_statement':'Farmers often struggle to maintain optimal growing conditions for crops due to changing weather patterns and environmental limitations. Traditional greenhouses can be expensive to operate.','proposed_solution':'Sustainable Greens is a smart greenhouse that automatically monitors and adjusts environmental conditions using sensors and automation technology. By tracking soil moisture, temperature, and humidity in real time, the system creates ideal growing conditions for different plant species.','tags':['SDG 2 - Zero Hunger','SDG 9 - Industry, Innovation and Infrastructure'],'season':'Season 5'},
